#!/usr/bin/env Rscript

# ==============================================================================
# TCR multimer QC and final EBV CD8 TCR object generation
# ==============================================================================
#
# Purpose:
#   This script takes the EBV-only VDJ CSV and EBV CD8 Seurat object generated by
#   8_generate_TCR_combined_rds.R and performs TCR/multimer QC.
#
#   It:
#     1. collapses VDJ contig rows into one row per cell,
#     2. resolves cells with multiple TRA/TRB chains using UMI counts,
#     3. joins Seurat metadata onto the TCR table,
#     4. performs within-sample tetramer conflict QC,
#     5. optionally applies manual VDJdb-resolved within-sample calls,
#     6. performs global/public-clone tetramer conflict QC,
#     7. optionally applies manual VDJdb-resolved global calls,
#     8. removes HLA-mismatched tetramer calls,
#     9. projects baseline GEM tetramer calls onto activated/non-GEM cells,
#    10. adds final TCR/tetramer metadata back to the Seurat object,
#    11. annotates tetramers with EBV antigen/lifecycle information,
#    12. performs CD8 gating for global PBMC cells, and
#    13. saves final publication-ready RDS files.
#
# Expected inputs:
#   - 8_merged_ebv_vdjs.csv
#   - 8_merged_EBV_CD8_samples_only.rds
#   - EBV_multimer_information.xlsx (available on 10.5281/zenodo.21231183)
#   - Tetramer_HLA_match.xlsx (available on 10.5281/zenodo.21231183)
#   - HLA_information.xlsx (available on 10.5281/zenodo.21231183)
#
# Manual QC inputs (available in Supplementary_inputs_for_scripts on 10.5281/zenodo.21231183):
#   - Conflicting_clones_per_sample_post_vdjdb.xlsx
#   - global_conflicting_TCRs_post_vdjdb.csv
#
# Notes:
#   - Manual VDJdb files are optional. If they are not present, the script uses
#     automatic majority rules when unambiguous and leaves unresolved conflicts
#     flagged in the output CSVs.
#   - Clone definition is TRB-based:
#       within-sample clone = sample + TRB_v_gene + TRB_j_gene + TRB_cdr3
#       global clone        = TRB_v_gene + TRB_j_gene + TRB_cdr3
#   - TCR rows are matched back to Seurat using the stable VDJ barcode key created
#     in 8_generate_TCR_combined_rds.R.
#
# ==============================================================================


# ----------------------------- #
# 0. Load packages
# ----------------------------- #

